<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Any component which must manipulate headers before "output is sent" (per the explanations found with many of PHP's functions that manipulate headers) probably can not be combined during the same execution of phpunit, as most of these components would eventually result in output sent (e.g. the periods), and thus prevent later components from manipulating the headers, <em>unless</em> output buffering (in php.ini) is appropriately utilized by each test suite.</p>

<p>Some people are reporting problems with the unit tests associated with headers, see <a href="http://www.php.net/headers_sent">http://www.php.net/headers_sent</a></p>

    </div>
